2. Rust crate dependencies
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

The Omnira desktop application is built with Rust and depends on third-party
crates (Tauri, tokio, rusqlite, serde, and others).

To generate an aggregated license report:

  powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/packaging/aggregate-licenses.ps1

This writes `THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.dependencies` at the repo root. Re-run after
dependency changes and include that file with release artifacts when publishing
alpha builds. Requires `cargo install cargo-license` and npm `license-checker`
(via npx).

Until the appendix is generated, section 1 (llama.cpp) remains the hand-maintained
bundled-runtime attribution required in every installer.

